        "score": 0.6116271,
        "text": "The document outlines requirements for establishing communication between a DSASP Provider and the New York ISO. Key points include:\n\n1. **Communication Configuration**:\n   - Required if the DSASP Provider's total enrollment is \u2264 25 MW.\n   - Involves one communications vendor, a set of network components, and one ICCP node.\n   - The DSASP Provider and NYISO must complete vendor agreements for direct communications.\n\n2. **Hardware and Software Requirements**:\n   - Establish a contract with a communications vendor to link to NYISO.\n   - Select circuit type, bandwidth, and obtain a Virtual Private LAN Service or MPLS.\n   - Identify network hardware, ensuring routers support encryption and firewalls are recommended.\n   - Software must support ICCP communication as both client and server.\n   - Configure hardware/software for ICCP Node, collaborating with NYISO personnel.\n   - Ensure scalability and redundancy, with systems designed for 99.99% availability.\n   - Identify necessary servers and hardware based on software vendor requirements.",
        "metadata": {
