        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Transmission and Dispatch Operations Manual, specifically focusing on \"Transmission Operations.\" It outlines the requirements and procedures for operating the NYS Transmission System, particularly when it is in a Normal or Warning State. Key areas covered include:\n\n1. **NYISO Controlled Transmission System Operating Limits**: \n   - **Thermal (Summer/Winter)**: Measured in MW, with categories for Normal, Long Term Emergency (LTE), and Short Term Emergency (STE).\n   - **Voltage**: Measured in kV, with pre-contingency and post-contingency high/low limits.\n   - **Frequency**: Measured in Hz, with normal high and low limits.\n   - **Interface Transfer**: Measured in MW, focusing on stability and voltage collapse.\n\n2. **Corrective Control Strategies**: \n   - Addresses major electrical network problems in the NYCA, such as facility overloads and excessive transfers, with solutions detailed in Figure 6.\n\nThe document also references tables and figures for further details on transmission facilities and corrective strategies.",
