        "text": "The document page outlines updates to the New York ISO Transmission and Dispatch Operations Manual as of April 28, 2016. Key changes include:\n\n- **Global Changes**: References to the \"NYISO Secured Transmission System\" were replaced with \"NYISO Controlled Transmission System.\"\n\n- **Section 2.1.6**: Updated references to the latest Reliability Rules & Compliance Manual.\n\n- **Section 2.2.1**: Removed language about certain Transmission Facilities not part of the NYISO Controlled Transmission System.\n\n- **Section 2.2.3**: Added a new section for Technical Bulletin #165 on communications through the Transmission Owner and renumbered subsequent sections.\n\n- **Section 2.2.5**: Added language on establishing System Operating Limits.\n\n- **Section 2.2.6**: Introduced subsections 2.2.6.1 and 2.2.6.2, incorporating Technical Bulletin #229 on default generator voltage schedules.\n\n- **Section 2.3.2**: Clarified existing language.\n\n- **Section 2.6.1**: Replaced language regarding NYISO Hotline communications with a reference to the Emergency Operations Manual.\n\n- **Section 3.1.2**: Revised periodic security assessment timing to every 60 seconds and removed a reference to \"Active RTD constraints.\"\n\n- **Section 3.1.6**: Corrected \"National Weather Bureau\" to \"National Weather Service.\"\n\n- **Section 3.1.9**: Removed a duplicate section on AVR and PSS outages, covered by the Outage Scheduling Manual.\n\n- **Section 5.1.1**: Deleted redundant and outdated language.\n\n- **Section 6.3.6**: Updated the middle pricing point value of Transmission Shortage Cost.\n\n- **Attachment C**: Removed as it was previously unused.",
