        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Transmission and Dispatch Operations Manual, version 3.0, dated 02/11/2016. It outlines updates and changes made to the manual, including:\n\n- Removal of references to NYISO non-firm transactions in various sections and tables.\n- Incorporation of details on ISO and transmission owner target voltage level programs, Interchange Scheduler Plus (IS+), and NYISO actions during neighboring control area TLR events.\n- Updates to demand curve values to reflect the graduated Transmission Demand Curve.\n- Inclusion of details on external transaction scheduling, curtailment notifications, and import transactions.\n- Relocation of footnotes and cross-references to the Ancillary Services Manual.\n- Inclusion of references to Southeastern New York reserve requirements and schedule changes for dispatch units.",
