        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Emergency Operations Manual, specifically \"Attachment A: Operating Criteria.\" It outlines several tables and an attachment related to operational guidelines:\n\n- **Table A-1**: Lists exceptions to the NYSRC Reliability Rules.\n- **Table A-2**: Lists bus voltage limits.\n- **Table A-3**: Lists pre-contingency low limits for various HQ to NYISO transfers.\n- **Table A-4**: Lists multiple circuit tower lines in the New York Control Area.\n- **Table A-5**: Lists the NYISO thunderstorm multiple contingencies.\n- **Table A-6**: Lists the IROL Interfaces.\n- **Attachment A.7**: Provides the NYISO System Operating Limit Methodology and procedures for relieving potential overloads on non-ISO controlled NERC Bulk Electric System (BES) facilities.\n\nA note indicates that these attachments do not require committee approval and are subject to change at NYISO's discretion.",
