        "score": 0.5849241,
        "text": "The document outlines communication protocols and responsibilities between Aggregators, Transmission Owners (TO), and the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO). Key points include:\n\n- **Metering and Telemetry**: Must be provided to the TO according to NYISO and TO requirements.\n- **Curtailments**: Any actions to preserve transmission system safety must be communicated to the Aggregator and NYISO promptly.\n- **Audits**: The TO must communicate with the Aggregator during NYISO-initiated audits as per specific procedures.\n\n**Communication Between TO and NYISO**:\n- Aggregation communications to NYISO and TO must be simultaneous.\n- Real-time communications about Aggregation operations should occur between the TO's operating desk and NYISO control room.\n- Notifications for Supplemental Resource Availability (SRA) for reliability are required.\n- TO must notify NYISO if curtailment is necessary for system security.\n- TO must communicate with NYISO during audits.\n\n**Communication Between Aggregator and NYISO**:\n- Aggregators receive updated schedules and instructions from NYISO under SRA rules.\n- Aggregators must submit offers reflecting Aggregation capabilities and report outages to NYISO market applications, responding to dispatch signals.",
