        "score": 0.57830673,
        "text": "The document page outlines procedures and criteria related to outage scheduling and system reliability for the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO).\n\n**NYISO Actions:**\n1. Modify the existing Outage Schedule as needed, including conducting necessary reliability studies based on the required extension time.\n2. Notify affected Transmission Owners (TOs) about rescheduling or canceling prescheduled outage requests due to extensions.\n3. Update and post the revised schedule on OASIS and update daily reports.\n\n**Transmission Owner Actions:**\n1. If an outage extension does not meet the minimum notification requirements, notify the NYISO Grid Operations Department immediately to assess the impact on system reliability.\n2. If the extension meets the minimum notification requirements, notify the NYISO Scheduling Department.\n\n**System Reliability and Transfer Criteria:**\n- The NYISO uses approved Outage Schedules to determine operating transfer limits for monitored interfaces.\n- Internal Interfaces include: Western NY Export, Dysinger East, West Central, Oswego Export, Moses South, Central East, Total East, UPNY/ConEd, and Sprainbrook/Dunwoodie South.\n- External Interfaces are also considered but not listed on this page.",
