        "id": "a722e5a1-9dec-4470-8f6d-043b45ed2dd9",
        "score": 0.57779676,
        "text": "The document outlines compliance standards for Distribution Providers (DP) and Generator Operators (GOP) as per NERC requirements. \n\n### NERC Distribution Provider (DP) Standards Compliance\n- **Communication Requirements**: Distribution Providers must maintain communication capabilities to convey critical information to the Reliability Coordinator, Balancing Authority, or Transmission Operator. The NYISO is registered with NERC as the Reliability Coordinator and Balancing Authority for New York.\n- **Operations Communications**: Communication between the NYISO and each Distribution Provider is conducted through the interconnected Transmission Owner to provide timely information for managing local transmission and security.\n- **Compliance to NERC Standards**: Distribution Providers must communicate conditions and status as required by NERC Standards through their Transmission Owner. The NYISO ensures this information is provided.\n\n### NERC Generator Operator (GOP) Standards Compliance\n- **Communication Requirements**: Generator Operators and Aggregators must convey critical status information and changes directly to the Transmission Operator without delay. The NYISO is registered as the Transmission Operator for New York.\n- **Operations Communications**: Communication between the NYISO and each Generator Operator and Aggregator is through the interconnected Transmission Owner. This system has been in place since NYISO's inception and serves to inform both the Transmission Owner and NYISO of generator parameters and statuses. Resources can establish communication pathways for electronic basepoints and metering with the NYISO.\n\nA link to the NYISO Direct Communications Manual is provided for further details.",
